This script is running on the **LSF (Load Sharing Facility)** system, a batch processing system. It utilizes several LSF commands, such as `#BSUB`, to set job parameters, including queue, job name, cores, GPU, wall time, memory, email notifications, and output/error files.

The script requires the **CUDA 11.6** module and executes a Python 3 script named **main.py**.  It uses the **resnet20_optimal_transport.yaml** configuration file and processes the **cifar10** dataset. The script also uses a checkpoint file located at **"/zhome/b2/8/197929/GitHub/CBS/checkpoints/resnet20.ckpt"** for restoring weights.  The script runs experiments under the **"exp_oct_21_resnet20_ot"** sweep, saving logs and CSV files in specific directories within **"/zhome/b2/8/197929/GitHub/CBS/prob_regressor_results/"**.

In summary, this script is a batch job submitted to the LSF system, utilizing CUDA, Python, and specific libraries to perform tasks related to a ResNet20 model on the CIFAR-10 dataset. It uses a pre-defined sweep name and saves results in specific locations.
